Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.48,0:00:07.11,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Koi wa thrill, shock, suspense
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.48,0:00:07.11,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Song by Rina Aiuchi
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.73,0:00:07.15,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,KOI WA THRILL, SHOCK, SUSPENSE
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.36,0:00:10.74,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,MIENAI CHIKARA TAYORI NI
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.86,0:00:18.28,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,KOKORO NO TOBIRA TOZASAZU NI TSUYOKU... TSUYOKU...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.33,0:00:21.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A courageous heart and deduction power!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.20,0:00:22.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rhythm that leads us to the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.16,0:00:24.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A pond that changes color with time...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.79,0:00:26.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dyed red, the case is solved!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.71,0:00:30.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Recognizing that one truth, a child with the mind of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.30,0:00:32.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.38,0:00:36.30,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,WATASHI GA KANJITEITA
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.89,0:00:47.06,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,TOGE OKIMI NI NO ONAJI\NYOU NI ATAETEITA NO KANO SHIRENAKATTA
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.15,0:00:57.99,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,NANI NI KOKORO WO ITAMETE NANI NI OBIETEITA NO KA\NKI NI INO TOMEZU MOTSURETEKU FUTARI NO SHINJITSU NI
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.53,0:00:58.12,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Opening Theme
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.53,0:00:58.12,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,「Koi wa thrill, shock, suspense」
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.12,0:01:01.54,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,MUKIAU NO GA KOWAKATTA
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.37,0:01:06.87,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,THIS LOVE IS A THRILL, SHOCK, SUSPENSE
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.00,0:01:14.13,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,MAYOI WO AOI KAZE NI CHIRASOU TOSHITE MO KAKAEKIREZU NI ITA YO
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.26,0:01:17.64,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,KONO CHISANA MUNE NI WA
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.76,0:01:21.22,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,KOKORO NO TOBIRA TOZASAZU NI
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.35,0:01:25.77,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,TSUGI E TO SUSUMU ARATA NA FUAN TO
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.89,0:01:34.99,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,MAYOI WO KAKAETESHIMAISOU NI NATTE MO
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.37,0:01:45.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We came as the substitutes for Sonoko\Nand her father, the Suzuki president,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.66,0:01:49.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and decided to attend a tea meeting at the Aonogi house.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.58,0:01:56.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the backyard of the mansion, there\Nwas a pond that shined in five colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.30,0:02:01.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there was a bridge which led to the tea room.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.39,0:02:05.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While we were enjoying the pond's colors,\Nsomething unusual happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.81,0:02:08.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The headmaster died in the tea room, the same way as the legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.81,0:02:10.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.65,0:02:13.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This isn't a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.44,0:02:15.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.44,0:02:23.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone here used a clever trick to kill the\Nheadmaster and made it look like a suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.12,0:02:26.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who on earth is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.95,0:02:30.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The {\i1}real{\i0} demon who blames it on a demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.58,0:02:38.30,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,The Water Palace of Five Colors
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.58,0:02:38.30,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,(Part 2)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.67,0:02:39.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.01,0:02:43.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When all of you gathered in this room after four o'clock,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.26,0:02:49.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you saw the headmaster's body from this veranda, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.60,0:02:53.73,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Antique Dealer
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.60,0:02:53.73,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Morio Yakura (42)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.64,0:02:53.56,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Yes. The pond was turning red.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.15,0:02:58.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, Ryoichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} checked the time on his watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.61,0:03:01.36,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Yes. It was exactly four o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.57,0:03:05.08,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Ryoichi Aonogi (28)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.57,0:03:05.08,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Headmaster's Son
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.99,0:03:06.29,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,At that time, I looked in the tea room,\Nbut my father's body was not there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.49,0:03:11.12,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Yoshiko Hanasaki (40)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.49,0:03:11.12,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Housekeeper
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.49,0:03:11.12,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Yukari Mimura (33)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.49,0:03:11.12,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Company President
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.79,0:03:10.79,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, Mimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came back and\Nwe discovered the body immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.37,0:03:14.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where was everyone at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.50,0:03:17.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was in the bath for thirty minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.88,0:03:21.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had some stuff to do so I went out for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.68,0:03:23.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where did you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.97,0:03:27.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's my personal matter. I don't need to answer that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.85,0:03:30.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about you, Hanasaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.27,0:03:34.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Getting ready for tonight in the kitchen and entertaining the guests.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.15,0:03:37.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ryoichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, where were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.32,0:03:41.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went in and out of the guest room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.03,0:03:46.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard the headmaster burned your precious fishing rods?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.12,0:03:49.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.08,0:03:51.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What exactly happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.17,0:03:56.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, I was told to participate in tonight's tea ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.67,0:04:00.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What he was planning to do was...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.09,0:04:04.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...to make me the next headmaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.43,0:04:07.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you don't know anything about tea ceremonies!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.89,0:04:12.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're kidding, right? I can't believe Master\Nwould say something like that now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.52,0:04:16.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Ryoichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. Did you accept?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.90,0:04:18.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course not, I refused.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.36,0:04:25.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means the headmaster burned your fishing\Nrods because you wouldn't listen to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.95,0:04:29.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and you hated the headmaster for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.66,0:04:31.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.50,0:04:32.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yokomizo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.96,0:04:38.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the headmaster died, everyone, including\NRyoichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.46,0:04:39.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.88,0:04:43.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if someone went out to murder him,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.30,0:04:46.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we probably would have seen them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.01,0:04:50.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was sitting on that chair the whole time,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.72,0:04:53.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but there was no one heading towards the tea room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.73,0:04:59.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means... they all have perfect alibis.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.36,0:05:03.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I wonder what Mimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} brought from outside...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.78,0:05:09.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was glancing around nervously, but she\Nprobably didn't have the time to hide it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.37,0:05:12.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which would mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.04,0:05:17.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.26,0:05:27.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it. Just as I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.59,0:05:34.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I have a cup of water? Oh, sorry I'm so thirsty.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.89,0:05:35.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.48,0:05:37.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.31,0:05:40.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to make tea for everyone anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.44,0:05:46.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Hanasaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.90,0:05:48.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.41,0:05:52.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why won't Ryoichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the only son, succeed to the headmaster?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.83,0:05:54.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.91,0:05:58.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're only a kid. It's none of your business.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.21,0:06:02.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's true. Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.25,0:06:04.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to become like my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.88,0:06:09.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was arrogant, and my mother had\Nto go through many hardships.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.68,0:06:16.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the position for headmaster has been passed down for many\Ngenerations, so naturally, wouldn't he want his son to succeed?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.48,0:06:21.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you become headmaster, you can make speeches\Nand teach classes to earn lots of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.56,0:06:26.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Teacups that have been passed down for many\Ngenerations also belong to the headmaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.86,0:06:29.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My father was only interested in that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.91,0:06:36.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you take over, you can still live the same life after you retire, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.33,0:06:42.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't like that side of my father. Hanasaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I'll help.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.54,0:06:43.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.79,0:06:47.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you were that miserable, you should've left the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.42,0:06:48.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.92,0:06:53.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Well, I was out for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.72,0:06:58.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I made him come back because I couldn't\Ntake care of the master by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.52,0:07:00.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.89,0:07:06.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We made a deal, so I didn't have to succeed to the headmaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.15,0:07:10.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My father didn't have anyone to reply on accounting,\Nso he said if I did that, it was okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.74,0:07:15.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see... But then he brought the subject back up?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.95,0:07:21.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Accounting... You know how much money\Nthe Aonogi household has, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.87,0:07:22.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.83,0:07:24.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.13,0:07:31.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the headmaster died while the next headmaster\Nwas undecided, you would take over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.34,0:07:35.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then the headmaster's position and you would become free.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.56,0:07:38.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was the real reason you came back home?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.27,0:07:47.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pardon me! Master was in an unhealthy\Nstate! He's worried about his father!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.82,0:07:52.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whatever. Thank you, Hanasaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. Then, I'll take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.91,0:08:04.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the headmaster, who's afraid of the demon,\Nshut himself up in the tea room with talismans.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.08,0:08:08.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he didn't like others going near the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.84,0:08:13.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. For that, we've set up security sensors.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.30,0:08:18.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So there's a very small chance that an outsider can get in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.85,0:08:23.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true. Around the tea room is a lake...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.73,0:08:28.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If someone crossed this bridge, someone\Nwould have noticed from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.82,0:08:31.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did the culprit...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.82,0:08:32.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.78,0:08:40.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're giving expensive ceramics and trying\Nto act innocent. Master is not that dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.08,0:08:42.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look who's talking!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.70,0:08:44.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have an eye on being the headmaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.16,0:08:47.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're investing money to the point where\Nyour company is not doing well!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.00,0:08:52.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute. We're only asking about his personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.38,0:09:01.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this teacup? Hanasaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, there's a crack in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.43,0:09:04.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm terribly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.06,0:09:09.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were probably too worried about the appearance\Nand didn't even bother to look at the other side, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.65,0:09:12.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Worried about the appearance!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.49,0:09:17.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now now, everyone's upset right now, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.57,0:09:22.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really? Hanasaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, aren't you happy that Master is dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.58,0:09:28.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He made his wife, who loved you dearly,\Nsuffer and have a shorter life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.17,0:09:30.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.59,0:09:35.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hanasaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did her very best for Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.97,0:09:42.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh. You two didn't lead Master to commit suicide\Nby scaring him with those legends?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.35,0:09:44.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What are you saying!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.47,0:09:46.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How awful!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.23,0:09:48.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hanasaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.94,0:09:56.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hanasaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.44,0:09:59.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't bear a grudge...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.62,0:10:04.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it. It's a common thing\Nfor Mimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to say things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.66,0:10:07.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this the wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.92,0:10:10.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She looks very kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.46,0:10:15.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was a very kind person.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.67,0:10:18.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just looking at her picture cheers me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.97,0:10:21.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why there are so many pictures of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.81,0:10:26.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She didn't blame me even if I hated tea ceremonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.68,0:10:29.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She would even come fishing with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.81,0:10:34.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This knot...!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.91,0:10:51.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Found it. Looks like someone forced their way here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.67,0:10:54.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If my deductions are correct...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.22,0:11:04.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.39,0:11:10.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So then the culprit would have to be that person who\Nwas acting awkwardly when the body was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.27,0:11:15.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There should be some evidence that the culprit left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.49,0:11:22.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.62,0:11:24.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.37,0:11:26.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The frozen evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.45,0:11:30.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, thank you everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.66,0:11:32.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we can go home now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.50,0:11:35.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. It's probably a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.25,0:11:36.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.59,0:11:37.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.46,0:11:40.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan, we're going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.26,0:11:41.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.84,0:11:43.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He should be coming down right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.97,0:11:51.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm done~. Well, I should go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.56,0:11:54.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sounds great! After one nap.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.86,0:12:01.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All we have to do now is wait for the inquest's results.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.07,0:12:02.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.82,0:12:10.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!! Uncle says, "Are you letting\Nthe culprit leave right in front of you?"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.75,0:12:12.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Culprit!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.33,0:12:14.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad figured it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.46,0:12:20.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does this mean, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.09,0:12:25.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You actually realized it, right, Inspector Yokomizo?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.01,0:12:31.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The headmaster did not commit suicide; he was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.89,0:12:34.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you please explain it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.73,0:12:39.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a good thing the famous detective\Nis here. It's a good way to kill time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.27,0:12:42.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, let's make this up to the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.82,0:12:48.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While the pond was turning red, there was\Na crime that none of you were aware of.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.66,0:12:54.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when the body was discovered, everyone was in this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.41,0:12:55.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you explain that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.87,0:12:56.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.17,0:12:59.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While the culprit was in this room,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.67,0:13:02.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he hung the headmaster from the beam in the tea room...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.05,0:13:05.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...using one rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.42,0:13:07.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.18,0:13:08.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Rope?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.64,0:13:18.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like the legend of this pond, the culprit stabbed\Nthe headmaster at the veranda of the tea room,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.06,0:13:21.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and strangled him from behind to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.32,0:13:27.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he hung the rope which was hidden\Nsomewhere in the room on the beam,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.78,0:13:31.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and made a knot that would tighten in one pull.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.74,0:13:34.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He tied one end around the headmaster's neck,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.79,0:13:41.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the other around the pillar, then out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.25,0:13:50.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He tied that rope to another rope which he had tied beforehand\Non the waterwheel that was hidden beneath the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.64,0:13:59.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He then could prepare for the time trick. Finally, on the entrance\Ndoor, he created a spring with thumbtacks and rubber bands.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.77,0:14:05.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He pulled it, used the hook to hang the scroll as a\Nstopper, and used the scroll to uphold the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.82,0:14:11.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After setting up a locked-room murder, the culprit left the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.29,0:14:19.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, there was a pinhole on the inner side of the entrance door.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.96,0:14:21.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.21,0:14:26.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, the culprit came back to this room and made an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.30,0:14:28.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How creepy! Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.76,0:14:35.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Around 4:00, the pond turned red,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.18,0:14:39.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the waterwheel started turning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.31,0:14:42.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then the rope winded. The body\Nwas dragged into the tea room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.81,0:14:50.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The body hit the scroll near the door, causing\Nthe scroll to fall and the door to shut.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.86,0:15:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The panel became locked in the post's hole. After the\Nbody was pulled up to the beam, the rope tightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.46,0:15:08.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cut that was measured beforehand ripped. The\Nrope was dragged outside by the waterwheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.42,0:15:13.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While we were shocked to find the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.68,0:15:19.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the cuplrit pretended to put the door aside and\Ntook off the rubber bands and thumbtacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.06,0:15:24.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. That's possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.31,0:15:27.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the waterwheel turns,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.36,0:15:31.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the sun made a diffused reflection which\Nmakes the rope harder to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.78,0:15:36.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit used this for the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.53,0:15:41.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did the murderer go in the tea room?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.50,0:15:44.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Through the bridge that we were looking at.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.79,0:15:53.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Weren't you the one who said that no\None went to the tea room, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.39,0:15:58.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"You were too concerned about the front,\Nso you didn't look at the other side."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.51,0:16:03.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that what you said, Mimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.98,0:16:04.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.15,0:16:07.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.44,0:16:09.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit used that blind spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.73,0:16:18.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While he left us gazing at the pond, he boldly went\Nto the tea room... underneath the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.49,0:16:20.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.49,0:16:24.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He hid in the shrubs beside the pond and crept under the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.25,0:16:30.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, he swam to the tea room underneath the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.21,0:16:33.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, he came up in front of the entrance door on the veranda.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.84,0:16:39.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He then lured the headmaster out of the\Nroom and stabbed him with a knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.72,0:16:41.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who is the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.22,0:16:46.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit was acting very strangely around\Nthe time when the headmaster was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.35,0:16:49.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, that's you. Saying that you went out!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.98,0:16:53.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Are you saying I'm the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.61,0:16:56.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll explain to us this time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.91,0:16:58.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.62,0:17:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only went to get this!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.37,0:17:05.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that an expensive teacup?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.83,0:17:08.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.83,0:17:14.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew that the headmaster was going to retire tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.34,0:17:19.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Weren't you afraid that Yakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} might become headmaster?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.85,0:17:27.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you hurried to go buy an expensive teacup\Nthat was better than Yakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.69,0:17:29.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Mimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.86,0:17:36.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, most of the money here goes\Nto me if I become the headmaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.99,0:17:38.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got a little greedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.53,0:17:42.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's probably the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.08,0:17:46.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she went out and sneaked back in, the alarm would go off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.21,0:17:53.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Mimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came, Hanasaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went\Nout and escorted her up the stairs, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.96,0:17:57.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, there was no time for\NMimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to go near the tea room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.55,0:18:01.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means Mimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is not the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.01,0:18:06.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.64,0:18:20.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit knew that no one would go near the headmaster,\Nwho was busy setting up for tonight's ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.61,0:18:23.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He hung the headmaster's neck in a special way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.08,0:18:27.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A Cleat Hitch knot. Fishermen use it when they moor the boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.75,0:18:29.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fishing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.96,0:18:31.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.50,0:18:33.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.50,0:18:38.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, the culprit swam underneath the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.92,0:18:44.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! He must have been wet! Hair and body!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.01,0:18:49.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To trick us, he took a bath after he committed the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.02,0:18:54.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. The culprit is you, Yakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.90,0:19:05.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we all gathered in this room, you were harshly blaming\NMimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, to the point where we had to stop you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.58,0:19:14.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was probably because you didn't want us\Nto see the moment the body was lifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.96,0:19:17.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you were so serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.21,0:19:22.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, all you had to do was wait\Nfor someone to notice the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.51,0:19:27.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! Those are guesses! You don't have any proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.35,0:19:36.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Admit your crime already. You left proof for us. On the bridge!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.98,0:19:39.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! The thing you asked for was there!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.78,0:19:40.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.99,0:19:44.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was under the bridge!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.41,0:19:49.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Handprints! What is this black thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.83,0:19:51.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the moss in the pond.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.58,0:19:54.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought that if someone passed there...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.46,0:19:57.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...there would be some marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.30,0:20:01.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were so many handprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.09,0:20:03.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think we may be able to get fingerprints!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.34,0:20:06.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The investigators are searching!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.64,0:20:10.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, Yakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, but may we have your fingerprints?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.35,0:20:15.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought it was a perfect plan...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.06,0:20:19.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You admit it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.78,0:20:25.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man was the worst!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.91,0:20:30.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He told you that you were going to be the next\Nheadmaster and you believed him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.58,0:20:31.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.96,0:20:39.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Together, we made fake expensive ceramics and sold them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.96,0:20:42.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.38,0:20:46.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't know? We've been doing it for over ten years.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.22,0:20:53.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he started believing that his wife's\Ndeath and the demon were related.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.18,0:20:57.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He changed. He was planning to officially make Ryoichi headmaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.90,0:21:03.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wanted to stop him before he made an official announcement.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.61,0:21:07.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because he made that kind of tea room...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.66,0:21:16.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look! It turned out to be exactly like the legend!
